page.title: 12Nutnell's Wood
page.content: Nutnell's Wood & Coalpit Coppice like Pepper Wood are ancient woodland. It has wild service & small leaved lime trees. The trees we saw were red wood, common & sessile oak, holly, common birch & fir trees. In Nutnell's Wood the flowers are buttercups, bluebells, germander speedwell, fox gloves, blue- bell fruits, black bryony, yellow pimpernel, wood spurge, forget me not, wood mellick, goose grass, meadow vetchling, birds foot trefoil, herb robert, stitchwort, wood violet, lesser clover, field rose, wild straw- berry, angelica, silver weed, willow herb, honeysuckle, night shade, herb bennet, dandelion, & compact rush. The bushes are guelder rose, hazel, hedge maple, grey sallow & dog wood. The paths in Nutnells wood were muddy. Mr Fincher, our guide is 80 & writes a weekly column for Bromsgrove Messanger
